00:14:32.921 --> 00:14:57.801
Incoming livestream: Let's talk about some of the lessons we learned along the way. First one, our major hurdle was the observability gap. So in the beginning, we had these engineering logs that told us what happened, but the security telemetry didn't really tell us who or which agent was responsible for what in a way that supported what we wanted to do, which was high-fidelity detection. So your mission here really is what we call identity multitasking.


116
00:14:58.101 --> 00:15:18.010
Incoming livestream: You have to partner with your engineering and product teams early on to ensure that your authentic logs aren't just debug strings, they need to be structured events that link the invoking user ID to the agent ID. Because without this context, you're blind to the, abuse of a legitimate agency case, where


117
00:15:18.171 --> 00:15:23.961
